# Windsurf Rules

Coding standards for production Python projects. Full details in CLAUDE.md.

## Context

- Python 3.10+ with pipenv
- Ruff + mypy + pytest
- Conventional Commits with mandatory scopes
- Docusaurus documentation
- GitHub Actions + Release Please

## Standards at a Glance

**Style**: Ruff (88 chars), PascalCase/snake_case, Google docstrings
**Types**: 100% coverage, Python 3.10+ syntax, Pydantic v2
**Testing**: pytest, 80%+ coverage, FIRST principles
**Git**: Conventional Commits, mandatory scopes from PROJECT_SCOPES.md
**Architecture**: src/ layout, Single Responsibility, DI, custom exceptions
**Docs**: Docusaurus, memory bank, Mermaid C4 diagrams

## Commit Scopes (Mandatory)

Your project scopes:
- `cli`, `playbook`, `schema`, `registry` (core)
- `analyzer`, `analyzer/*` (11 variants)
- `report`, `templates` (rendering)
- `ci`, `deps`, `docs` (tooling)

Full list with details: PROJECT_SCOPES.md

## Quick Commands

```bash
ruff format .              # Format code
ruff check . --fix         # Lint and fix
mypy src/                  # Type check
pytest --cov=src           # Test with coverage
```

## Code Rules Checklist

- [ ] Code is typed (mypy strict)
- [ ] Tests added (80%+ coverage)
- [ ] Ruff passes (`ruff check .`)
- [ ] Docstrings present (public functions)
- [ ] Commit uses correct scope
- [ ] Commit subject is functional, present tense
- [ ] No `print()` (use logging)
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets
- [ ] No global state (DI pattern)
- [ ] Error handling with domain exceptions

